Message.MsgText: Migrate.InvalidClusterName=CWWSG1020E: Invalid Cluster Name.
Message.Explanation: The user has entered a string on the command line to represent the cluster name. The entered cluster name is not valid
Message.UserResponse: Check for typing errors then re-issue the command with the cluster you wish to use.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.InvalidNodeName=CWWSG1019E: Invalid Node Name.
Message.Explanation: The user has entered a string on the command line to represent the node name. The node name is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Check for typing errors then re-issue the command with the node you wish to use.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.GatewayAlreadyExists=CWWSG1022E: Gateway {0} already exists in bus {1}.
Message.Explanation: There is already a Gateway with the specified name configured in the specified bus.
Message.UserResponse: Rerun the migration script specifying a unique Gateway Instance name.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.MissingArgument=CWWSG1006E: Missing Argument {0}.
Message.Explanation: The user has omitted the installation directory, cell name or server name from the command line argument list.
Message.UserResponse: Re-issue the command using all the required fields.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.NodeFileMismatch=CWWSG1015E: There must be one node name for each file.
Message.Explanation: The user has entered a backup file name on the command line without a node name.
Message.UserResponse: Re-issue the command with a valid node name for each backup file.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.InvalidFile=CWWSG1007E: Invalid file {0}.
Message.Explanation: The backup file that was given on the command line is not valid, contains errors or omitted data.
Message.UserResponse: Try recreating the backup file.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.MultipleNonUniqueWSDLServices=CWWSG1010E: Multiple services with same name: {0}.
Message.Explanation: WSDL file is not valid as it contains multiple services with the same name.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the WSDL file or obtain a valid version then re-issue the command.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.BusFileMismatch=CWWSG1005E: There must be one bus name for each file.
Message.Explanation: The user has entered a backup file name on the command line without a bus name.
Message.UserResponse: Re-issue the command with a valid bus name for each backup file.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.InvalidArgument=CWWSG1004E: Invalid argument {0}.
Message.Explanation: The user has entered an unrecognized argument on the command line.
Message.UserResponse: Check for typing errors the re-issue the command without the unrecognized argument.

Message.MsgText: BackupFile.FileIOException=CWWSG2001E: File {0} threw an IOException.
Message.Explanation: The file probably doesn't exist. The error is likely to have been caused by a typing error on the command line.
Message.UserResponse: Check for typing errors in the Gateway backup file stated on the command line and re-issue the command with corrections.

Message.MsgText: BackupFile.UserChannelFound=CWWSG2002E: A user-defined channel {0} has been identified in the file {1}.
Message.Explanation: Only standard channels can be migrated using this utility, but an unrecognised channel has been found in the file.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the channel definition from the file and re-issue the command.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.SecurityRemoteHost=CWWSG1018E: Backup file contains security information but a remote administration hostname has been specified.
Message.Explanation: Backup files containing security information may only be migrated on the host containing the administration server.
Message.UserResponse: Rerun the migration command for this backup file on the host containing the administration server.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.ContainsFilters=CWWSG1023I: The backup file contains filters. These will not be migrated.
Message.Explanation: Gateway filters are no longer supported so they will not be migrated.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.InvalidAppServerRoot=CWWSG1001E: Invalid Root AppServer Directory.
Message.Explanation: The user has entered a string which is not valid, on the command line to represent the location of the AppServer root directory.
Message.UserResponse: Check for typing errors, then re-issue the command with the root directory of the AppServer.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.MigrationError=CWWSG1017E: Migration Error.
Message.Explanation: An unhandled error has occurred during the migration process.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: Migrate.NoWSDLPortsDefined=CWWSG1011E: No port elements defined for service: {0}.
Message.Explanation: WSDL file is not valid as the service contains no ports.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the WSDL file or obtain a valid version then re-issue the command.

Message.MsgText: GatewayOutboundXML.CouldNotCreateDestination=CWWSG2502E: Destination {0} could not be created.
Message.Explanation: The destination could not be created successfully.
Message.UserResponse: If problem recurrs, contact your IBM representative.

Message.MsgText: BackupFile.TooManyTargets=CWWSG2004W: More than one TargetServiceLocation found for Proxy Service {0}.
Message.Explanation: A proxy service should not have more than one target service in the Gateway backup file.
Message.UserResponse: Rerun the migration with a valid Gateway backup file.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.InvalidArgumentValue=CWWSG1016E: Invalid argument value {1} for argument {0}.
Message.Explanation: The user has entered a string on the command line which is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Check for typing errors then re-issue the command with the corrected argument.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.ServiceNotFoundInWSDL=CWWSG1012E: Service {0} not found in WSDL {1}.
Message.Explanation: WSDL File may be valid in itself but not for the required service. The specified service name was missing from this WSDL.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the WSDL file or obtain a valid version then re-issue the command.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.NoWSDLServicesDefined=CWWSG1009E: No service elements defined.
Message.Explanation: WSDL file is not valid as it contains no services.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the WSDL file or obtain a valid version then re-issue the command.

Message.MsgText: GatewayOutboundXML.CouldNotSetRouting=CWWSG2501E: The routing could not be set for destination {0}.
Message.Explanation: The destination could not have it's forward or reverse routing path set. Make sure the destination was created successfully.
Message.UserResponse: If problem recurrs, contact your IBM representative.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.InvalidCellName=CWWSG1002E: Invalid Cell Name.
Message.Explanation: The user has entered a string on the command line to represent the cell name. The cell name is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Check for typing errors then re-issue the command with the correct cell name.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.CantFindWSDL=CWWSG1008E: Could not find WSDL {0}.
Message.Explanation: The WSDL file for one of the services could not be found via HTTP.
Message.UserResponse: Turn on the server holding this WSDL and re-issue the command.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.InvalidServerName=CWWSG1003E: Invalid Server Name.
Message.Explanation: The user has entered a string on the command line to represent the server name. The server name is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Check for typing errors then re-issue the command with the server you wish to use.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.ArgumentIgnored=CWWSG1024I: The {0} argument is not required and will be ignored.
Message.Explanation: The specified argument does not have any effect.
Message.UserResponse: The specified argument may be safely omitted.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.NodeServerCluster=CWWSG1021E: Invalid Node/Server/Cluster combination
Message.Explanation: The user has entered a combination of node, server and cluster names on the command line which is not valid.
Message.UserResponse: Re-issue the command with either a node and server specified, or a cluster specified.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.HeaderNotValid=CWWSG1014E: The SOAPHeader field is invalid.
Message.Explanation: The SOAPHeader field in the backup file should be of the format namespaceURI:localPart.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the WSDL file or obtain a valid version then re-issue the command.

Message.MsgText: BackupFile.TooManyChannels=CWWSG2005W: More than one ChannelForService found for Proxy Service {0}.
Message.Explanation: A proxy service should not have more than one channel in the Gateway backup file.
Message.UserResponse: Rerun the migration with a valid Gateway backup file.

Message.MsgText: BackupFile.NoUDDIPassword=CWWSG2003E: No UDDIPassword has been found for UDDIReference {0}.
Message.Explanation: UDDIReferences with a publishURL specified must also have a user name specified. If no authentication is needed, the user name should be UNAUTHENTICATED.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the UDDIReference and re-issue the command.

Message.MsgText: Migrate.EEPANotValid=CWWSG1013E: The External End Point Address field is invalid.
Message.Explanation: The ExternalEndPointAddress field in the backup file should be of the format http://<server>:<portnumber>/.....
Message.UserResponse: Correct the WSDL file or obtain a valid version then re-issue the command.
